## Request

```bash
curl https://llm.bytespike.ai/v1/messages \
  -H "x-api-key: $BYTESPIKE_API_KEY" \
  -H "anthropic-version: 2023-06-01" \
  -H "content-type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "model": "{/* model_id */}",
    "max_tokens": 1024,
    "messages": [
      {"role": "user", "content": "Hello, who are you?"}
    ]
  }'
```

{/* For OpenAI-protocol models, the equivalent shape is:
```bash
curl https://llm.bytespike.ai/v1/chat/completions \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer $BYTESPIKE_API_KEY" \
  -H "content-type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "model": "{/* model_id */}",
    "messages": [{"role": "user", "content": "Hello, who are you?"}]
  }'
```
Pick the protocol that matches the vendor's native shape; both work for
every model on the gateway.
*/}

### Body parameters

| Field | Type | Required | Default | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| `model` | string | yes | — | `{/* model_id */}` |
| `messages` | array | yes | — | Conversation history. |
| `max_tokens` | integer | yes | — | Hard cap on response length. Max for this model: {/* 4096 / 8192 / 32768 / etc. */} |
| `system` | string \| array | no | — | System prompt. Array form supports `cache_control`. |
| `temperature` | number | no | 1.0 | Range 0.0–1.0. |
| `top_p` | number | no | 1.0 | Nucleus sampling. |
| `tools` | array | no | — | {/* "Supported" / "Not supported" / "Beta" */}. |
| `tool_choice` | object | no | `{"type":"auto"}` | {/* delete row if tools not supported */} |
| `stream` | boolean | no | false | SSE streaming, see [Streaming](#streaming). |
| `{/* model-specific */} ` | {/* type */} | no | {/* default */} | {/* e.g. `thinking` for Anthropic reasoning models, `reasoning_effort` for OpenAI o-series */} |

## Response

```json
{
  "id": "msg_{/* … */}",
  "type": "message",
  "role": "assistant",
  "model": "{/* model_id */}",
  "content": [
    {"type": "text", "text": "{/* example response text */}"}
  ],
  "stop_reason": "end_turn",
  "usage": {
    "input_tokens": {/* N */},
    "output_tokens": {/* N */}
  }
}
```

### Response fields

| Field | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `id` | string | ByteSpike-issued message ID. |
| `model` | string | Echoes the request `model`. |
| `content` | array | Always at least one block. Text in `{"type": "text", ...}`; tool calls in `{"type": "tool_use", ...}`. |
| `stop_reason` | string | `end_turn` / `max_tokens` / `tool_use` / `stop_sequence`. |
| `usage.input_tokens` | integer | Prompt tokens billed. |
| `usage.output_tokens` | integer | Generated tokens billed. |
| `usage.cache_read_input_tokens` | integer | {/* delete if model doesn't support cache_control */} |

Headers always present on every response (success + failure):

```
X-RateLimit-Limit: {/* USD cap, e.g. 50.00 */}
X-RateLimit-Remaining: {/* USD remaining */}
X-RateLimit-Reset: {/* Unix ts */}
X-Quota-Remaining-Credits: {/* USD lifetime remaining */}
```

Per-call cost via [`/api/v1/me/usage`](/api-reference/account/me-usage).

## Code examples

<CodeGroup>

```bash cURL
curl https://llm.bytespike.ai/v1/messages \
  -H "x-api-key: $BYTESPIKE_API_KEY" \
  -H "anthropic-version: 2023-06-01" \
  -H "content-type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "model": "{/* model_id */}",
    "max_tokens": 1024,
    "messages": [{"role": "user", "content": "Summarize the first chapter of Moby Dick."}]
  }'
```

```python Python
import anthropic

client = anthropic.Anthropic(
    base_url="https://llm.bytespike.ai/v1",
    api_key="$BYTESPIKE_API_KEY",
)

message = client.messages.create(
    model="{/* model_id */}",
    max_tokens=1024,
    messages=[
        {"role": "user", "content": "Summarize the first chapter of Moby Dick."}
    ],
)

print(message.content[0].text)
```

```javascript Node
import Anthropic from "@anthropic-ai/sdk"

const client = new Anthropic({
  baseURL: "https://llm.bytespike.ai/v1",
  apiKey: process.env.BYTESPIKE_API_KEY,
})

const message = await client.messages.create({
  model: "{/* model_id */}",
  max_tokens: 1024,
  messages: [
    { role: "user", content: "Summarize the first chapter of Moby Dick." },
  ],
})

console.log(message.content[0].text)
```

</CodeGroup>

## Streaming

Set `"stream": true`. Response is SSE in the standard Anthropic format
(or OpenAI format if you called `/chat/completions`). The estimated
credits header ships in the HTTP response before the first event, so you
can short-circuit a long completion before paying for it. See
[Streaming](/concepts/streaming) {/* TODO: link to concept page if it exists */} for the full event sequence.

## Cache control

{/* Delete this section if the model doesn't support prompt caching.
     Otherwise: confirm the cache_read multiplier in the pricing table. */}

`cache_control` blocks reduce cost on repeated prompts. Cache reads are
billed at the discounted rate visible in the
[pricing table](https://bytespike.ai/pricing#text) under "cache read".

```json
{
  "model": "{/* model_id */}",
  "system": [
    {
      "type": "text",
      "text": "{/* long static system prompt */}",
      "cache_control": {"type": "ephemeral"}
    }
  ],
  "messages": [...]
}
```

## Errors

| Code | Trigger | Billed? |
|---|---|---|
| 400 | Body validation failed | No |
| 401 | Missing / revoked key | No |
| 402 | Wallet exhausted | No |
| 403 | Scope denied / IP not allowlisted | No |
| 422 | Param not supported by this model (e.g. `tools` on a non-tool model) | No |
| 429 | Rate-limited at the gateway tier | No |
| 5xx | Upstream provider issue | No (auto-retry envelope) |

Error envelope follows the protocol you called — Anthropic shape on `/v1/messages`, OpenAI shape on `/v1/chat/completions`. See [Errors reference](/concepts/errors-reference) for the full status + code matrix.

